item.title: I found these cool photos on a discarded hard drive
item.dc:creator: Cup_o_Joe
item.description:
Now here are the photos of the mutimedia computer I built for 564$ in 2007

Motherboard (ECS 761gxM754) + CPU (Sempron 3400+)= 69$ (discount from usual 110$ because the Pentium 4 motherboard I bought failed and fried my processor)
DVD drive = 30$
Asus Geforce 8500GT Silent = 85$
2GB of OCZ DDR400 RAM = 80$
7.1 Channel PCI sound card = 0$ (gift)
Floppy drive = 0$
case and power supply = 50$ total
Fans = 58$ in total.
CPU cooler = 25$
card reader = 30$
fan grills = 5$
spray paint (black and white) = 20$
metal handles = 10$
IDE Hard Drive swap = 17$
500GB Seagate Barracuda SATA Hard Drive = 85$

With all those fans blowing the hot air out from the back and the side, the temperatures are:

Via Chipset 28C to 32C
IDE 30C to 34C
SATA 28C to 30C
Sempron 29C to 35C
Video Card 40C to 47C

So the computer will last a while since it’s cool and quite silent.
